\displaystyle E\left[\frac{1}{1+X}\right]=\log\left( (1-p)^{\frac{p}{p-1}}\right)
E\left[\frac{1}{1+X}\right]=\log p^{\frac{p}{p-1}}
log(1-x)=-\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{x^n}{n}
-\sum_{y=1}^{\infty}\frac{(1-p)^y}{y}=log(1-(1-p))=\log(p)
E\left[\frac{1}{1+X}\right]=\sum_{x=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{1+X}p(1-p)^x=\sum_{y=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{y}p(1-p)^{y-1}=-\frac{p}{p-1}\sum_{y=1}^{\infty}\frac{(1-p)^y}{y}
=\frac{p}{p-1}\log p
1-p
